tions Plc \u2013Board Member\nNigeria Inter-bank Settlement Systems Plc.- Board Member\n\n==EFCC crises==\nEconomic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) invaded the bank on the account of the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) imposed a \u20a62.4 billion fine on the bank for the role it allegedly played in the MTN Nigeria illegal funds repatriation to South Africa though the visitation was not legal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://guardian.ng/news/efcc-storms-standard-chartered-bank-lender-describes-visit-as-baseless/|title=EFCC storms Standard Chartered bank, lender describes visit as baseless|date=15 September 2018|publisher=|access-date=11 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329074532/https://guardian.ng/news/efcc-storms-standard-chartered-bank-lender-describes-visit-as-baseless/|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Standard Chartered got the highest fine of N2,470,604,767.13 and the CBN has since debited the bank.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2018/09/14/breaking-efcc-operatives-storm-standard-chartered-banks-head-office/|title=Breaking: EFCC Operatives Storm Standard Chartered Bank\u2019s Head Office|first=|last=editor|date=14 September 2018|publisher=|access-date=11 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002031330/https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2018/09/14/breaking-efcc-operatives-storm-standard-chartered-banks-head-office/|archive-date=2 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Wilson Uwajaren, spokesman of the EFCC, said there was no attempt to arrest Adesola.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thecable.ng/efcc-officials-storm-head-office-of-standard-chartered-bank|title=EFCC officials storm head office of Standard Chartered Bank|date=14 September 2018|website=TheCable|access-date=11 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329074449/https://www.thecable.ng/efcc-officials-storm-head-office-of-standard-chartered-bank|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cit